data.description: Price to Sale! Motivated Seller! Country Living at its finest on this beautiful 17.24 acre Farm in the foothills of the Great Smoky Mountains. This amazing property gives you a little bit of everything, you have 3 pastures, hardwood forest, small bamboo forest, seasonal creek, small pond, and plenty of room to plant your own orchard, and add beehives for amazing fresh honey. This large 2-bed/2-bath 2-story 1600sqft farmhouse sits on top of a knoll right in the middle of the property with lots of privacy. Large 900sqft walkout basement is used as a mudroom and storage that could be converted into another living space.  Included are two barns for keeping machinery, hay, horses, cattle, goats, or even maybe those adorable llamas out of the elements of nature. There's a chicken coop to raise those cute Fancy Feet for fresh eggs and endless entertainment. Abundance of wildlife to watch and/or hunt. Walking the property you will find Persimmon trees, PawPaw trees, wild blackberries, black raspberries, and a robust garden full of amazing vegetables. This property would qualify for Greenbelt Status (15acres or more.) Come live the country lifestyle on this beautiful farmstead in Newport TN. Close to Cherokee National Forest, Panther Creek State Park, Cherokee Lake, Douglas Lake, Pigeon River, French Broad River and Nolichucky River for endless hiking, mountain biking, fishing and waterfall exploring. Outdoor activities are endless and just a short drive from the farm. Short drive to major towns and cities, like Knoxville TN (1hr drive), Ashville NC (1hr+ drive), Johnson City/Tri-Cities (1hr drive), and Gatlinburg/Pigeon Forge TN (1hr drive). Easy access to town for provisions, Morristown (1/2hr drive/160N), and Newport (15min drive/160S). Minutes to Interstate 40 and Interstate 81.
